cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on datacenter networks and inter-datacenter transfers, which are networking-related topics. 
2. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper discusses cloud computing services, which are distributed and often involve parallel and cluster computing. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a scheduling technique for meeting service level agreements and deadlines, which can be considered a control problem. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a new algorithm for traffic allocation, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms. 
5. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper discusses improving the utilization of WAN resources and meeting service level agreements, which are related to performance.
